 <br>
I was born the son of a Teir'Dal Warrior and Warrioress in the city of Neriak.<br>
Being a fairly small and weak child i was not well suited to the warrior's life they had chosen for me, and was a source of constant dissapointment to them. Although my dexterity and skill with a blade was unmatched whilst practicing manoeuvres, i was unable to take on the other students in a face to face confrontation.<br>
On one day after a particularly humiliting defeat at the hands of another student i was told to leave the warrior's guild and never return.<br>
After i broke the news to my parents that i would never become a warrior, and would never follow in their footsteps, they became enraged, beating me bloody and unconcious.<br>
I woke later that evening in a pool of my own blood on the floor where they had left me. Aching all over i gathered up all the hatred in me to give me strength.<br>
Taking a knife from the kitchen i proceeded to sneak to my parents room, knowing one noise, one creaking board, would be the end of me.<br>
I stood over their bed watching silently, as they lay sleeping, totally unaware of the fate which was to befall them.<br>
I reached over and held the knife a hairs breadth from my fathers throat, before dropping the blade and pulling back sharply. My mother was awake instantly, but her swing was not even halfway to my head before she shared the same fate. Standing back i admired my handiwork as their movements slowed to small twitches. I had done well to get so close to these two experienced warriors and kill them both in but a few seconds, without taking a single blow. Licking the blood from my blade i set out that night, with nothing but the clothes on my back and that small knife, to make my fortune. <br>
There was a whole world out there, and it owed me.... <br>
